Key Match Events: Tim David hit a boundary on the final ball to secure a six-wicket win for Australia.
Mitch Marsh scored 72 off 44 balls to steer Australia towards the target.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was Australia's third-best T20 chase, but they also set a record for conceding more than 200 in four consecutive T20 internationals.
Others: Rachin Ravindra scored 68 off 35 balls, Devon Conway scored 63 off 46 balls, and Finn Allen scored 32 off 16 balls for New Zealand.
